[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there in Mathlib a Float.Pi like Real.Pi that is defined as a floating point number and is computable?</p>",
        "id": 507634629,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1742783892
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The file <code>Init/Data/Float.lean</code> in Lean's source code contains the basic definitions for <code>Float</code>. There doesn't seem to have constants for Pi or <code>e</code>.</p>\n<p>You could potentially define your own with:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fPi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">atan2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/--</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">info: 3.141593</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">guard_msgs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fPi</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 507897227,
        "sender_full_name": "Walter Moreira",
        "timestamp": 1742860409
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm looking at the documentation and Float.atan2 and other functions are defined as \"opaque\". What does opaque mean?</p>",
        "id": 507902199,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1742863190
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That you can't use its definition in a proof</p>",
        "id": 507904942,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1742864830
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it possible to do something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">π</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">atan2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 509335636,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1743470693
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"628490\">Colin Jones ⚛️</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Is.20there.20a.20Float.2Epi/near/509335636\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is it possible to do something like this:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">π</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">atan2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, but it will have to be <code>noncomputable</code></p>",
        "id": 509337812,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1743471975
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So pointless if I wanted to use it as a Float?</p>",
        "id": 509338576,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1743472392
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can do something similar with typeclasses that does compute.</p>",
        "id": 509338668,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1743472439
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for example purposes</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HasPi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"π\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HasPi</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">noncomputable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HasPi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">HasPi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">atan2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">π</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi_eq_pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">π</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 509339223,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1743472734
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thank you!</p>",
        "id": 509346663,
        "sender_full_name": "Colin Jones ⚛️",
        "timestamp": 1743476592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was just thinking about this.  Why isn’t there a Float.pi?  If Float is 64 bit, we know the closest binary value to pi (<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/72365104/the-most-accurate-approximation-of-pi-in-ieee-754-float64\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/72365104/the-most-accurate-approximation-of-pi-in-ieee-754-float64</a>).  If Lean just uses the current C version of floats, then can’t we just use that, or is this not part of the C standard?</p>",
        "id": 541156778,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Rute",
        "timestamp": 1758697754
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Also, I see this isn’t the best stream for this discussion as this is the #maths stream.)</p>",
        "id": 541156783,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Rute",
        "timestamp": 1758697757
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, it seems c doesn’t have a standard for pi (<a href=\"https://langdev.stackexchange.com/questions/2075/what-obstacles-prevented-c-and-c-from-standardizing-π\">https://langdev.stackexchange.com/questions/2075/what-obstacles-prevented-c-and-c-from-standardizing-π</a>), but still most languages support it, and I think there is an ieee standard for what it should be.</p>",
        "id": 541162908,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Rute",
        "timestamp": 1758699928
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just checked and the <code>atan2 0 (-1)</code>and <code>0x1.921fb54442d18p1</code> definitions are the same (at least on <a href=\"https://live.lean-lang.org/\">https://live.lean-lang.org/</a> server).</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">-- trig def</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">atan2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- 64-bit precision: 0x1.921fb54442d18p1 = 56593902016227520 x 2^(-54)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofBinaryScientific</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">56593902016227520</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">54</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- higher precision: 0x3.243f6a8885a308d313198a2e03707344ap0L = 68417829380157871863019543882359730131240 x 2^(-134)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofBinaryScientific</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">68417829380157871863019543882359730131240</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">134</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi0</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- 3.141593</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi1</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- 3.141593</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi2</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- 3.141593</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- check if bits are the same</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi0</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toBits</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- 4614256656552045848</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi1</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toBits</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- 4614256656552045848</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Float</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">pi2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toBits</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- 4614256656552045848</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 541190397,
        "sender_full_name": "Jason Rute",
        "timestamp": 1758708314
    },
    {
